		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/11/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 08:35:43</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=5502"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5502')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4872&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Hybrid+cast+time+reduction+%2D+Why%3F"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I'm not the type of person to whine about what other classes have, hell I think everyone should be uber as possible, but wtf is up with these hybrid cast time reductions?</P><P>Why can a tank who is supposed to be like 1/4 necro, cast some of my best spells (like Drain Soul and Cascading Darkness) in half the cast time?  Unresistable melee dmg + no xp penalty anymore + no extra mana cost anymore + 1/2 the cast time on all my spells?  Why?</P><P> Really pisses me off, not because I want anyone else nerfed, some the hybrids had it very tough at the beginning, just why cant we get the same reduction if its not unbalancing (which it obviously isnt).</P><P><p><font face="Arial" color="#ff9900" font size="2"><palign="center"><strong>Retrievil Hesevil<br><BR>'If you have a problem, if no one else can help, and if you can<BR>find him, maybe you can hire ... The Evil One.'<br><BR>-Tallon Zek -</p></font></td>

      </tr>

