        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="38662"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/11/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 10:11:27</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=1310"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1310')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=38662&amp;TOPIC_ID=4872&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Hybrid+cast+time+reduction+%2D+Why%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Combination of things really.</P><P>A: Hybrids casting the same spells a pure-caster does spends more mana doing it.  I don't mean just from the screwed fizzle rates on hybrids, I mean there is a built in modifier to cost.</P><P>This extra-mana cost has been in from the start of the game, and won't be going away any time soon, sadly.  The change you may remember where Verant brought this up was when the mana pool was changed to have the wis/int equal that of the level of a pure caster. </P><P>Example; before change: 9th shadow knight w/ 100 int has the mana pool of a 1st necro w/ 100 int. After change: 9th sk w/ 100 int = 9th necro w/ 100 int.</P><P>B: Casting time was reduced so hybrids would actually use their spells during combat.  Hybrids found, and verant agreed, that DPS was penalized for using spells, even if the spell hit for full in case of a DD. The haste isn't 1/2 btw.</P><P>This help shed a little light? Just a quick response, lots more about hybrid if you really wanna open up the can of worms.</P><P>----</P><P>Naeamael Soulflayer, 56th</P><P>"They may hate me, so long as they fear me." <BR>- Machiavelli<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

